msgstr ""

#: ../effects.rst:518
msgid "Gamma is the way video systems brighten or darken the midtones of an image. **Rec 709** is the standard gamma curve used for most HD and online video today. By shipping with **Rec 709** LUTs, OpenShot makes it simple to apply a grade that matches the vast majority of footage you’ll edit."
msgstr ""

#: ../effects.rst:522
msgid "If your camera or workflow uses a different gamma (for example a LOG profile), you can still use a LUT made for that curve. Simply use a `.cube` file designed for your gamma under the Color Map effect’s **LUT Path**. Just be sure your footage gamma matches the LUT gamma—or the colors may look incorrect."
